Certainly! Let's walk through the limitations of ThreadGroup in Java with proper explanations and examples, so you understand why itâ€™s discouraged and what alternatives are better.

ğŸ”» 1. Obsolete and Discouraged by Java
âŒ Limitation:
The ThreadGroup class is outdated. The Java API documentation itself advises against using it, recommending ExecutorService and other concurrency tools instead.

ğŸ” Java Docs (ThreadGroup): "This class is obsolete. Use the java.util.concurrent package instead."

âœ… Example:
java
Copy
Edit
