for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
    new Thread(group, () -> {
        System.out.println("Running task: " + Thread.currentThread().getName());
    }).start();
}
This is inefficient, as it creates 5 new threads instead of reusing them.

âœ… Modern Alternative (Executor):
java
Copy
Edit
