for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
    executor.submit(() -> {
        System.out.println("Running task: " + Thread.currentThread().getName());
    });
}
executor.shutdown();
Here, threads are reused and managed automatically.

ğŸ”» 3. No Reliable Exception Handling
âŒ Limitation:
ThreadGroup does not handle uncaught exceptions well. If a thread crashes, thereâ€™s no way for the group to catch and handle it centrally.

âŒ Example:
java
Copy
Edit
