This is dangerous â€” threads can become unresponsive.

âœ… Better Practice:
Use volatile flags or Future.cancel(true) with tasks in ExecutorService.

ğŸ”» 5. Inaccurate Monitoring APIs
âŒ Limitation:
Methods like activeCount() and enumerate() give approximate results â€” not thread-safe and not accurate under concurrency.

âŒ Example:
java
Copy
Edit
